<div type="definition">
<p>EAGER to POSSESS MORE than one NEEDS.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current abstract term for an exaggerated desire for the possession of things of all kinds is tān 貪 (ant. lián 廉 "morally pure and ungreedy").</p>
<p>2. Lán 婪 and the late and rare chán 饞 refer specifically to the exaggerated desire for food and drink.</p>
<p>3. Tāo 饕 (often used with tié 餮 as the proper name of a mask figure) are highly archaic and elevated words to use for greediness for food and drink.</p>
        </div>
